text: Unemployment rates in six states, including NY, reached a new 40-year low in February.
Texas and six other states saw a year-over-year decline in GDP from Q4 2019 to Q4 2019.
In February, average private-sector weekly earnings ranged from MS’ $765 to DC’s $1,750.
Iowa and five other states saw a year-over-year decline in private employment in February.
In February, the unemployment rate was above 5% in only three states and DC.
Through February 2020, Utah’s year-over-year job growth has exceeded the US average since 2010.
Nine states saw a year-over-year decline in state and local public employment in February.
Illinois’s annual house price growth has trailed the US average each quarter since 2009.
Idaho and Utah had the largest increases in house prices between Q4 2018 and Q4 2019.
